      "During the visit, homeowners should expect a clear explanation in plain language. If the repair is straightforward, the next step should be equally clear. If parts are needed, there should be no confusion about what is being replaced or why. Transparent diagnostic pricing also matters, especially when the diagnostic fee is waived with completed repair, because it removes some of the uncertainty that often delays service decisions.",
